definition.value: Any D-aldose having a six-carbon chain with a phosphate group at C-6.
A member of the class of pyrazines that is pyrazine in which one of the hydrogens is replaced by a cyclohexylmethyl group.
An octadecadienoic acid in which the two double bonds are at positions 9 and 12 and have Z (cis) stereochemistry.
A mandelamide in which the stereocentre at position 2 has R-configuration.
